signals.name: INV_Modulation_Index
signals.comment: This is the modulation index. The scale factor is x100. To get the actual modulation index divide the value by 100.

signals.name: INV_Flux_Weakening_Output
signals.comment: This is the current output of the flux regulator.

signals.name: INV_Power_On_Timer
signals.comment: Updated every 3 msec. This will roll over in approximately 150 days!

signals.name: INV_Parameter_Response_Addr
signals.comment: Address of parameter response message data.

signals.name: INV_Parameter_Response_Data
signals.comment: Data from parameter message.  All data is 16 bits and is contained in bytes 4 and 5. Bytes 6 and 7 should be ignored.

signals.name: VCU_INV_Parameter_Address
signals.comment: Address of parameter to be written or read.

signals.name: VCU_INV_Parameter_Data
signals.comment: Data to be written.  All data is 16 bits and is contained in bytes 4 and 5.

signals.name: VCU_INV_Torque_Command
signals.comment: Torque command when in torque mode

signals.name: VCU_INV_Speed_Command
signals.comment: Speed command used when in speed mode

signals.name: VCU_INV_Speed_Mode_Enable
signals.comment: 0 = No change to mode, 1 = change to speed mode from torque mode

signals.name: VCU_INV_Rolling_Counter
signals.comment: Rolling Counter sent to inverter.  If used increment count with each message sent.  Otherwise can be set to 0.

signals.name: VCU_INV_Torque_Limit_Command
signals.comment: Torque Limit, set to 0 to keep default

signals.name: INV_Post_Fault_Lo
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: INV_Post_Fault_Hi
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: INV_Run_Fault_Lo
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: INV_Run_Fault_Hi
signals.comment: Each bit represents a fault. Please refer to PM100 Users Manual for details.

signals.name: INV_VSM_State
signals.comment: Different states for the vehicle state machine

signals.name: INV_Inverter_State
signals.comment: Different states for the inverter state machine

signals.name: INV_Self_Sensing_Assist_Enable
signals.comment: 1 = Self Sensing Assist Enabled, 0 = Self Sensing Assist Disabled

signals.name: INV_Inverter_Discharge_State
signals.comment: 0 = Disabled, 1 = Enabled, 2 = Speed Check, 3 = Active, 4 = Complete, 5 = Error, 6 = Override, 7 = Timeout

signals.name: INV_Direction_Command
signals.comment:
1 = Forward
0 = 'Reverse' if inverter enabled  & 'Stopped' if inverter is disabled

signals.name: INV_Limit_Max_Speed
signals.comment: Indicates that torque is being modified to limit the speed.

signals.name: INV_Limit_Hot_Spot
signals.comment: Indicates that torque is being limited to limit the hot spot temp

signals.name: INV_Low_Speed_Limiting
signals.comment: Indicates that motor current is being limited due to low motor electrical frequency.

signals.name: INV_DC_Bus_Voltage
signals.comment: The actual measured value of the DC bus voltage

signals.name: INV_Output_Voltage
signals.comment: The calculated value of the output voltage, in peak line-neutral volts

signals.name: INV_VAB_Vd_Voltage
signals.comment: Measured value of the voltage betwen phase A and Phase B

signals.name: INV_VBC_Vq_Voltage
signals.comment: Measured value of the voltage between Phase B and Phase C

signals.name: INV_Phase_A_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase A current

signals.name: INV_Phase_B_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase B current

signals.name: INV_Phase_C_Current
signals.comment: The measured value of Phase C current

signals.name: INV_Motor_Angle_Electrical
signals.comment: The Electrical Angle of the motor as read by the encoder or resolver

signals.name: INV_Motor_Speed
signals.comment: The measured speed of the motor

signals.name: INV_Electrical_Output_Frequency
signals.comment: The actual electrical frequency of the inverter

signals.name: INV_Delta_Resolver_Filtered
signals.comment: Used in calibration of resolver angle adjustment.

signals.name: INV_Stall_Burst_Model_Temp
signals.comment: Hottest temperature estimated from the stall burst thermal model feature

signals.name: INV_Torque_Capability
signals.comment: The torque capability of the inverter given the current operating point.
